
1) What is the difference between the Thread and Runnable?
Thread is a class. Runnable is an interface.

2) How do you start a thread using Runnable?
1. implement the Runnable interface
2. extend the Thread class

3) How do you start a thread using Thread?
Thread thread = new Thread("name");
thread.start()


4) How do you get a thread's name?
???

5) What does the "synchronize()" method do?
- allows two or more threads access to a shared resource that can be used only by one thread.

6) What doe the "join()" method do?
join() allows the thread to wait until the thread on which it is called terminates. also allow you to specify a maximum amount of time that you want to wait for the specified thread to terminate.
- the calling thread goes into a waiting state and remains there until the referenced thread terminates

7) What does the "sleep()" method do?
to pause the execution of current thread for specified time in miliseconds

8) What is the one method you must write if you're implementing the Runnable class?
run()

9) Should you create that same method if you're extending Thread?
No?

10) Why is multi-threading so cool?
You can execute multiple programs at once!
